SEM_JOB COMMAND_NAME varchar 64 Hard-coded English string that indicates which command was launched. This is the same string placed in the XML for pre-defined name.

Update_Now = Update content.
ScanNow_Full = Do a full scan.
ScanNow_Quick = Do an Active Scan.
ScanNow_Custom = Do a custom scan.
Update_ScanNow_Full = Update content and then do a full scan.
Update_ScanNow_Quick = Update content and do an Active Scan.
Update_ScanNow_Custom = Update content and do a custom scan.
CancelScan = Cancel the scan.

SERVER_ADMIN_LOG_1 ERROR_CODE int 4  √  null Can uniquely identify the error in the source code (only used when an exception is related to this event).

Error codes:
ERROR_CODE_x00000000 = OK
ERROR_CODE_x10010000 = Unexpected server error.
ERROR_CODE_x10020000 = Failed to connect to Server.
ERROR_CODE_x11010000 = Invalid session.
ERROR_CODE_x12010000 = The action type is null.
ERROR_CODE_x12020000 = The action type is invalid.
ERROR_CODE_x12030000 = The object GUID is null.
ERROR_CODE_x12040000 = The object GUID is invalid.

AGENT_SECURITY_LOG_1 HACK_TYPE int 4  √  null If event ID = 209, Host Integrity failed (TSLOG_SEC_NO_AV), the reason for the failure
If Event ID = 206, Intrusion Prevention System( Intrusion Detected, TSLOG_SEC_INTRUSION_DETECTED), the intrusion ID
If event ID = 210, Host Integrity passed( TSLOG_SEC_AV), additional information

Possible reasons are as follows:

Process is not running - Bit0 is 1
Signature is out of date - Bit1 is 1
Recovery was attempted - Bit2 is 1
AGENT_SECURITY_LOG_2 HACK_TYPE int 4  √  null If the event ID is TSLOG_SEC_NO_AV, then it is one of the reasons listed below.
If the event ID is TSLOG_SEC_INTRUSION_DETECTED, it is intrusion ID.
If the event ID is TSLOG_SEC_AV, then it is additional information.

Reasons:

Bit0 is 1: Process is not running
Bit1 is 1: Signature is out of date
Bit2 is 1: Recovery was attempted
